Example 1. Father = full blood, Mother = full blood, Child = full blood<br>
<br>
Example 2. Father = full blood, mother = Half blood, Child = 3/4 blood<br>
<br>
Example 3. Father = half blood, mother = quarter blood, Child = 3/8 blood <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFF0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsaulttribe.showUserPublicProfile?gid=egoboy@saulttribe>egoboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#000000>(10/9/03 12:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Blood Quantum</span><hr size=1> Blood Quantum is not recognized by our Tribe. If adopted in full, one is as any other. Blood Quantum is a 'race' thing. It never ceases to shock me when I hear PHDs at major universities dicussing aspects of 'race' at length. There is culture, there is connection, but there is no 'race.' Nothing is sadder than the parents who went unrecognized because they were seen through a racist's eyes.<br>
<br>
In point of fact, some traditionals hold that the animals are our relatives and descended from us, hence modems, clans et cetera. The true history of the 'New World' is so buried by aspects of 'race' that it burdens the heart of the conversation. Keeping to 'scientific' orthodoxy has blinded many to the extent that it limits a healthy conversation regarding who first walked as a human in North America to those individuals who strode across an ancient land bridge. This ignores the peoples who have made the seas and the ice their highways.<br>
<br>
Meerly sharing a few thoughts on this evolving conversation <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCC0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsaulttribe.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jan@saulttribe>Jan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#000000>(1/19/04 2:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Blood Quantum</span><hr size=1> &lt;Blood Quantum is not recognized by our Tribe.&gt;<br>
<br>
Are you kidding me?<br>
<br>
&lt; Blood Quantum is a 'race' thing.&gt;<br>
<br>
That may be true and I understand what you are saying when you speak of those PHd's... but I do not see it as racist. <br>
<br>
Call me racist or call me whatever... but don't call me late for a meal... When BQ gets below 1/8th... that person is 7/8th of something else!!! I live in Abenaki country and part of the problems they have with getting State recognition is that they maintain the one drop rule. Cherokee's are also noted for this. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Having a connection with the people and culture are important factors, but some nation practice the &quot;adoption&quot; into a tribe. So... with that, when a non-Indigenous person is adopted into a tribe and made a member, should they also have the rights as the blood Indians? NO! Even if they know more about the culture and traditions than those of us who live outside of the Peoples Land? NO! <br>
<br>
One can blame the government for making this about race, but we have mongloids, caucasians and negroes. What are we? We are Chippewa... but how else do we identify ourselves in the race game? We are considered Indians by the masses and that makes a distinction between us and others.<br>
<br>
I DO believe in BQ and the reason I strongly believe in it is those who in the last 15 years who suddenly found being Indigenous as some kind of &quot;club&quot; that benefits from land and casino's. Look at the last census... and see the influx of native people. Do you really believe that? I say, poppycock! <br>
<br>
Ever heard the ones who found out that gr. gr. granny hid being an Indian and they just found out that they were Indian. Make no mistakes here... my mother couldn't hide that she was Indian, even if she tried as, she was full blood. My grandparent's couldn't either... but they never tried to hide their heritage. They were proud to be Chippewa... as I and my children are. I'm definately for the cut off of BQ... because there are just too many that lay claim to being Indian and yet cannot prove it.<br>
<br>
Jan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFF0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsaulttribe.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lunargoddess68@saulttribe>Lunargoddess68</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(1/20/04 9:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Frustrated...</span><hr size=1> Then there are some of us who are trying to prove our heritage but cannot get any cooperation from the proper channels.  My daughter's father is Chippewa and everytime I find him, he disappears again because he thinks I want child support from him.  When all I want is for my daughter to find her relatives.  She so desperately wants to be an official member of her tribe rightfully.  But we are hitting brickwalls.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCC0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsaulttribe.showUserPublicProfile?gid=egoboy@saulttribe>egoboy</A></span><br> Posts: 13<br> <font color=#000000>(1/26/04 12:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Frustrated...</span><hr size=1> I would never call anyone late for dinner!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=39.topic"> <img src="h